---
const steps = [
  { label: 'Explore', model: 'Haiku', sub: 'Find files', x: 60, color: 'var(--grey)' },
  { label: 'Plan', model: 'Opus', sub: 'Phased plan', x: 200, color: 'var(--accent-ink)' },
  { label: 'You approve', model: 'human', sub: 'Quality firewall', x: 360, color: 'var(--ink)' },
  { label: 'Implement', model: 'Sonnet', sub: 'Per phase + verify', x: 520, color: 'var(--accent)' },
  { label: 'Review', model: 'Opus', sub: 'P0/P1/P2/P3', x: 680, color: 'var(--accent-ink)' },
];
---

<section class="pipeline" id="what-it-does" aria-labelledby="pipeline-h">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow" data-reveal>How it works</span>
    <h2 id="pipeline-h" data-reveal>One task, the right model at every step.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead" data-reveal>
      <code>/yukti:smart &lt;task&gt;</code> classifies your request and runs it through a pipeline of specialist subagents. Code changes go through five stages — each on the cheapest model that does the step well. Analysis questions are answered directly in your current session, no extra wait.
    </p>

    <div class="diagram-wrap" data-reveal>
      <svg
        class="diagram"
        viewBox="0 0 740 220"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Pipeline diagram: explore, plan, you approve, implement, review"
      >
        <!-- Connector line - drawn via animation -->
        <path
          id="pipeline-track"
          d="M 60 100 Q 130 80, 200 100 T 360 100 T 520 100 T 680 100"
          fill="none"
          stroke="var(--grey-soft)"
          stroke-width="2"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-dasharray="4 5"
          class="pipe-track"
        />

        {steps.map((s, i) => (
          <g class={`pipe-step pipe-step-${i}`} transform={`translate(${s.x}, 100)`}>
            <circle r="22" fill="var(--paper)" stroke={s.color} stroke-width="2.4" />
            <circle r="6" fill={s.color} class="pipe-dot" />
            <text y="-32" text-anchor="middle" class="pipe-label" font-family="var(--font-display)">
              {s.label}
            </text>
            <text y="44" text-anchor="middle" class="pipe-model" font-family="var(--font-mono)" fill={s.color}>
              {s.model}
            </text>
            <text y="60" text-anchor="middle" class="pipe-sub" font-family="var(--font-body)" fill="var(--grey)">
              {s.sub}
            </text>
          </g>
        ))}
      </svg>
    </div>

    <p class="diagram-note" data-reveal>
      The orchestrator's tool list is restricted to <code>Agent</code>, <code>Read</code>, <code>Bash</code> — it physically <em>cannot</em> implement code itself. It can only delegate. That's enforced by the harness, not the prompt.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .pipeline {
    background: var(--paper);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--grey-line);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--grey-line);
  }
  .pipeline .container { padding-top: clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 5.5rem); padding-bottom: clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 5.5rem); }

  h2 { max-width: 16ch; }

  .section-lead {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 64ch;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .section-lead code {
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--grey-line);
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .diagram-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 1rem 0 2rem;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  }
  .diagram {
    width: 100%;
    min-width: 720px;
    height: auto;
    overflow: visible;
  }

  .pipe-label {
    font-size: 22px;
    fill: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .pipe-model {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .pipe-sub {
    font-size: 11px;
  }

  /* Initial state for animation */
  .pipe-track {
    stroke-dasharray: 800;
    stroke-dashoffset: 800;
  }
  .pipe-step { opacity: 0; transform-box: fill-box; transform-origin: center; }
  .pipe-dot { transform-origin: center; transform: scale(0); }

  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-track {
    animation: drawTrack 1.6s ease-out forwards;
  }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step {
    animation: stepIn 0.5s ease-out forwards;
  }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-0 { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-1 { animation-delay: 0.55s; }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-2 { animation-delay: 0.85s; }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-3 { animation-delay: 1.15s; }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-4 { animation-delay: 1.45s; }

  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-dot {
    animation: dotPop 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1) forwards;
  }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-0 .pipe-dot { animation-delay: 0.5s; }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-1 .pipe-dot { animation-delay: 0.85s; }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-2 .pipe-dot { animation-delay: 1.15s; }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-3 .pipe-dot { animation-delay: 1.45s; }
  .diagram-wrap.is-visible .pipe-step-4 .pipe-dot { animation-delay: 1.75s; }

  @keyframes drawTrack {
    to { stroke-dashoffset: 0; }
  }
  @keyframes stepIn {
    to { opacity: 1; }
  }
  @keyframes dotPop {
    to { transform: scale(1); }
  }

  .diagram-note {
    color: var(--grey);
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    max-width: 64ch;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1rem;
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0;
  }
  .diagram-note em { color: var(--ink); font-style: italic; }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .pipe-track { stroke-dashoffset: 0; }
    .pipe-step { opacity: 1; }
    .pipe-dot { transform: scale(1); }
  }
</style>
